parameters:
Former Imperial Dark Operative Alicia: H-Hic... Ahaha, I'm
fine, don't worry.

Sister Eleo: The smell of alcohol! I thought you were
seriously injured!

Former Imperial Dark Operative Alicia: Ahaha, I might have
a serious injury, you know?

Sister Eleo: Injured people don't get this drunk!
Seriously, come inside and rest.

Former Imperial Dark Operative Alicia: There are injuries
that you can't see, you know, young lady.

Sister Eleo: Healing that is also our job. Using alcohol to
heal is just a temporary mood booster, it doesn't heal the
heart.

Former Imperial Dark Operative Alicia: Impressive words...
I wonder if even someone like me can aspire to be a doctor.

Sister Eleo: Yes, of course! I will take care of you
properly.
Sister Eleo: I am Eleo. And you are?
Sophia: I... um, my name is Sophia. I am a little doctor.

Sister Eleo: Being little is unnecessary! Hehe, please come
in, Miss Sophia.

Queen Caron, who unleashed the Imperial Dark Operatives,
went on to kill her comrades. Instead of searching for Lex,
it was a struggle just to survive. Eventually, I began to
wonder if my days with Lex were nothing but an illusion.

With the worsening situation, the amount of wine consumed
increased. By drinking alcohol, I was able to dream of the
beautiful days I spent with Lex. However, I began to see the
nightmare of being dragged into a pool of blood again.

In a situation where I didn't know where I was or who I was,
Alicia had reached a point where she didn't even feel
despair anymore. It was at that moment that a small girl
called out to her.

The girl who would change Sister Eleo and Alicia's fate.
Her voice, her response, her spirit, everything about her
was dazzling. This girl felt like the version of herself
that never became a member of the Dark Operatives.

I felt embarrassed. It was as if my past self was watching
me. It felt like I was being questioned about my goal to
heal people.

It was natural to use a fake name to hide my true identity.
However, I was aware that it wasn't the only reason. I
didn't want to show my true self in her dazzling eyes.

And there was a faint hope that if I were with her, maybe I
could be reborn. Such feelings gave birth to the Cleric
Sophia.

Sister Sophia spent her days under Sister Eleo's guidance.
She learned from Eleo, was scolded by Eleo, and was amazed
by Eleo. The warm and peaceful days gave Sophia hope.

I'm sure that Lord Lex is alive and we will definitely be
able to reunite. Alicia pretended to be drunk, pretended to
go to the tavern, and investigated Lex's whereabouts
centered around the campus.

Fortunately, the campus was the stronghold of the Senate
noble, Pido, and even Queen Caron couldn't act recklessly in
such a place.

At the same time, Caron had conflicts with the Terios
Church, and the Terios Church served as a very convenient
hideout. However, it was also a situation that lacked a
decisive factor.

Alicia couldn't conduct a wide-ranging investigation and
couldn't involve Eleo and the others. She was waiting for an
opportunity. She believed that a chance would come, just
like the one that allowed her to escape from the torture
chamber in the past.

Alicia was under Eleo's guidance, waiting for that moment.
And the opportunity came in the form of Eleo's request. It
was a meeting with Clea and the others who would change
Alicia's fate.
Priestess Sophia: I apologize for the wait.
Clea: Were you able to say goodbye?

Priestess Sophia: Once again, I am Priestess Sophia. I will
be embarking on this journey with all of you.

Priestess Sophia: I will chase after the dragons with all
of you for the sake of heroic deeds.
Clea: Nice to meet you too, please take care of me.

For Alicia, joining forces with Clea and the others was
just one means. Achieving heroic deeds and confronting
dragons were merely expedients.

For Alicia, the greatest value of acting together was the
fact that Clea belonged to the Adventurer's Guild.

Alicia concluded that the Adventurer's Guild is somehow
involved in Lex's disappearance within the limited time.

If I act with Clea, there might be a chance to obtain some
information. Naturally, in the beginning, Sophia had no
sense of camaraderie. However, humans are constantly
changing beings.

Just as Lex changed Alicia, Sister Eleo changed Alicia.
Clea, Nora, and Relm also changed Alicia.

Alicia has obtained too many things to live ruthlessly. Her
hands are filled with shining memories overflowing. That is
why she must confess.

Even if it means being despised by my beloved comrades, I
will reveal Alicia's true self, her past, and her true
purpose. It is only natural that I face the consequences.
Both Alicia and Sophia came to the same conclusion.
